Design and Development of Drone for Rescue Surveillance and Disaster Management
When landslide occurs, immense efforts are taken to save the lives of those who are trapped underneath the landslide. During the landslide, drones equipped with a thermal imaging system can prove to be a significant tool to aid the rescue of trapped lives, but often the rescue efforts are delayed due to time taken for dispatch of these drone as the technology despite being popular, is not as readily available.
Miss. Prajakta Mahesh Chougule (group leader), Miss. Harshada Tanaji Kawale, Miss. Ankita Kumar Desai and Mr. Yash Raju Tale, students of DKTE‚Äôs Mechanical Engineering Department, tried to find solution for this exact problem. The proposed solution to tackle this problem is design and development of versatile SAR drone systems, offering a quick, adaptive and efficient setup for SAR operations. Under guidance of Prof. Dr.V. D. Shinde, this initiative aims to improve disaster response by quickly deploying drones for tasks such as landslide and flood surveillance, as well as firefighting in critical locations with limited human accessibility.
In the project undertaken, students have successfully designed and tested the firefighting module for small to medium-scale fires and low-rise buildings. The developed firefighting module has proven highly effective and adaptable, with a focus on scalability and affordability without compromising on performance. Also, students have contributed in addition of thermal camera in the drone to aid search and rescue operations by providing competitive accuracy and sufficient resolution. The integration of the thermal camera module has enhanced the drone's capability for SAR operations by providing the ability to detect heat signatures.
In conclusion, the versatility of the developed systems in diverse scenarios underscores its potential impact on mitigating the challenges posed by disasters, yielding considerable positive outcomes for rescue surveillance and disaster management operations. This project has received industrial sponsorship from Mr. Abhijit Chavan, proprietor of Total Tech Surveyors, a drone and aerial surveying firm and consultants in Kolhapur. Also, the project has been granted Rs. 15,000 for Research and Development by Ready Engineer MSME Scheme by Tata Technologies and Centre of Excellence, Gokul Shirgaon Manufacturers‚Äô Association.
This project received blessings from Chairman Kallappanna Awade, Vice-chairman and MLA Prakash Awade, Hon. Secretory Dr. Sou. Sapana Awade and all trustees of the institution. Special guidance was received from to Prof. Dr. L. S. Admuthe, I/C. Director, D.K.T.E. & Prof. Dr. V. R. Naik, Head, Department of Mechanical Engineering for completion of this project.

The Faculty of Computer Science convened with its esteemed alumni to engage in a fruitful discussion. The primary objective of this gathering was to glean valuable insights from our alumni, focusing on refining the curriculum, aligning it with current market demands, and enhancing support for their professional growth.

During the meeting, our alumni graciously shared their profound suggestions and shed light on the prevailing challenges within the job market. They expressed gratitude for the unwavering support offered by the department post-graduation. Moreover, they underscored the significance of continuous training and skill development to navigate the dynamic industry landscape. In response to these insights, the Department has pledged to organize customized career development training sessions to cater to the specific needs of our alumni.
These proactive measures are designed to equip our graduates with the requisite skills and knowledge to thrive in their careers and make valuable contributions to the realm of computer science. 
The session concluded on a note of optimism and collaboration, with both faculty and alumni reiterating their dedication to working in harmony towards shared success and progress in the ever-evolving technology domain.

Use CHAT GPT with GOOGLE DOCS. Total Game Changer!

The combination of Chat GPT and Google Docs indeed results in the perfect balance of AI. It brings together the power of natural language processing and collaborative document editing to enhance productivity and efficiency in today‚Äôs digital world.

Chat GPT (Generative Pre-trained Transformer) is a state-of-the-art artificial intelligence language model developed by OpenAI. It can generate human-like language and respond to natural language prompts, making it useful for a range of applications like virtual assistants or chatbots. When integrated into Google Docs, Chat GPT allows users to communicate with the document in a conversational style, providing a more natural and streamlined approach to editing and content creation.

Google Docs, on the other hand, is a cloud-based word processing tool that enables real-time collaboration between users. Multiple users can work on the same document simultaneously, and changes are automatically saved and synced across all devices. This creates a convenient and efficient way for teams to collaborate on documents without the need to send multiple copies back and forth.

The integration of Chat GPT and Google Docs provides a new level of collaboration and communication capabilities. Users can use the AI language model to suggest edits, ask questions, or receive feedback on the document they are working on. This can help to streamline the editing and review process, saving time and allowing for a more efficient workflow.
